title: The latest Windows Update is reportedly causing Starfield problems
description: The latest Windows update appears to be filled with issues, ranging from poor performance in games to straight-up crashes and blue screens.

title: Remarkable imagery shows NASA probe as it’s hit by a solar storm
description: A NASA spacecraft has for the first time flown through a solar eruption, capturing some remarkable imagery along the way.

title: X, formerly Twitter, looks set to become subscription-only
description: Elon Musk has said that as part of efforts to tackle the issue of bots on X, formerly Twitter, all users may be asked to pay a small monthly fee.

title: How to watch final moments of NASA’s first asteroid sample return mission
description: NASA will live stream the final moments of its groundbreaking OSIRIS-REx mission that will see it bring home samples collected from the Bennu asteroid in 2020.

title: Intel’s new integrated graphics could rival discrete GPUs
description: Intel has just made a huge leap forward in its graphics department. Going forward, integrated GPUs will have access to hardware ray tracing.

title: NASA’s amazing Mars helicopter just set a new flight record
description: NASA's Mars helicopter continues to impress. During its 59th flight on the distant planet, the drone-like machine achieved a new record.

title: Elon Musk’s Neuralink now recruiting for first human trials
description: Neuralink has announced that it’s now accepting applications from subjects willing to have its experimental N1 computer interface implanted in their brain.

title: Amazon is hiring a quarter of a million extra workers for the holiday season
description: Eyeing the upcoming holiday rush, Amazon has announced that it’s aiming to hire 250,000 warehouse and delivery workers, with a bump in the hourly pay offered.

title: NASA’s Artemis moon astronauts suit up for mission practice run
description: The four Artemis II astronauts who will embark on a flyby of the moon next year successfully conducted a pre-launch practice run on Wednesday.

title: Fujifilm’s new Instax Pal camera is fun, but pricey
description: Fujifilm has just unveiled the Instax Pal camera, a diminutive digital device targeted at teens who might want to print their pictures, too.
